## CORD-19: The Covid-19 Open Research Dataset

[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505)[Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841) [Sebastian Kohlmeier](/author/Sebastian-Kohlmeier/41018147)

Computer Science, Medicine

-   22 April 2020

The mechanics of dataset construction are described, highlighting challenges and key design decisions, an overview of how CORD-19 has been used, and several shared tasks built around the dataset are described.

## S2ORC: The Semantic Scholar Open Research Corpus

](/paper/S2ORC%3A-The-Semantic-Scholar-Open-Research-Corpus-Lo-Wang/5c5751d45e298cea054f32b392c12c61027d2fe7)

Computer Science

-   2020

In S2ORC, a large corpus of 81.1M English-language academic papers spanning many academic disciplines is introduced, which is expected to facilitate research and development of tools and tasks for text mining over academic text.

## MSˆ2: Multi-Document Summarization of Medical Studies

](/paper/MS%CB%862%3A-Multi-Document-Summarization-of-Medical-DeYoung-Beltagy/d25121da56c9050137800c69520111b30201d1ed)

[Jay DeYoung](/author/Jay-DeYoung/48727916)[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/46181066)[Madeleine van Zuylen](/author/Madeleine-van-Zuylen/15292561)[Bailey Kuehl](/author/Bailey-Kuehl/2003338023)[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505)

Medicine, Computer Science

-   13 April 2021

This work releases MSˆ2 (Multi-Document Summarization of Medical Studies), a dataset of over 470k documents and 20K summaries derived from the scientific literature that facilitates the development of systems that can assess and aggregate contradictory evidence across multiple studies, and is the first large-scale, publicly available multi-document summarization dataset in the biomedical domain.

## What Do We Mean by “Accessibility Research”?: A Literature Survey of Accessibility Papers in CHI and ASSETS from 1994 to 2019

](/paper/What-Do-We-Mean-by-%E2%80%9CAccessibility-Research%E2%80%9D%3A-A-of-Mack-McDonnell/9b8dbfe1e2c8a52307d8a2c20b65ba22e406c9ea)

[Kelly Avery Mack](/author/Kelly-Avery-Mack/91903310)[Emma J. McDonnell](/author/Emma-J.-McDonnell/2075900057)[D. Jain](/author/D.-Jain/37883312)[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505)[Jon E. Froehlich](/author/Jon-E.-Froehlich/145904884)[Leah Findlater](/author/Leah-Findlater/1689620)

Computer Science

-   12 January 2021

A dataset of accessibility papers appearing at CHI and ASSETS since ASSETS’ founding in 1994 is created and analyzed to understand current and historical trends and highlight areas that have received disproportionate attention and those that are underserved.

## TREC-COVID: rationale and structure of an information retrieval shared task for COVID-19

](/paper/TREC-COVID%3A-rationale-and-structure-of-an-retrieval-Roberts-Alam/85e60f8f947b4478a04dbd425cac32d2245c9b9c)

[Kirk Roberts](/author/Kirk-Roberts/1742509)[Tasmeer Alam](/author/Tasmeer-Alam/73544348) [W. Hersh](/author/W.-Hersh/1688124)

Computer Science, Medicine

J. Am. Medical Informatics Assoc.

-   4 May 2020

TREC-COVID differs from traditional IR shared task evaluations with special considerations for the expected users, IR modality considerations, topic development, participant requirements, assessment process, relevance criteria, evaluation metrics, iteration process, projected timeline, and the implications of data use as a post-task test collection.

## The Semantic Scholar Open Data Platform

](/paper/The-Semantic-Scholar-Open-Data-Platform-Kinney-Anastasiades/cb92a7f9d9dbcf9145e32fdfa0e70e2a6b828eb1)

[Rodney Michael Kinney](/author/Rodney-Michael-Kinney/143967880)[Chloe Anastasiades](/author/Chloe-Anastasiades/1667818755) [Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)

Computer Science

-   2023

This paper combines public and proprietary data sources using state-of-theart techniques for scholarly PDF content extraction and automatic knowledge graph construction to build the Semantic Scholar Academic Graph, the largest open scientific literature graph to-date.

[

## MedICaT: A Dataset of Medical Images, Captions, and Textual References

](/paper/MedICaT%3A-A-Dataset-of-Medical-Images%2C-Captions%2C-and-Subramanian-Wang/5ba77a5bdeffb62aa0902ae68997bbc38db8a722)

[Sanjay Subramanian](/author/Sanjay-Subramanian/17097887)[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505) [Hannaneh Hajishirzi](/author/Hannaneh-Hajishirzi/2548384)

Medicine, Computer Science

-   12 October 2020

Using MedICaT, a dataset of medical images in context, the task of subfigure to subcaption alignment in compound figures is introduced and the utility of inline references in image-text matching is demonstrated.
